 Family spokesperson Milly Mulelu said that the memorial will start at 10am.Hundreds of friends and fans are expected to fill the theatre to pay tribute to the Is Good Is Nice actor who died in a car accident on Saturday evening.The family said funeral arrangements have not yet been finalised.A bakkie collided with Joe s Ford Figo at around 10pm on Saturday. The star was declared dead by paramedics on the scene and a case of culpable homicide was opened.